Running spdk perf on lightbox

1. compile perf
    cd $WORKSPACE_TOP/spdk/examples/nvme/perf
    dockerize make CONFIG_DPDK_DIR=$WORKSPACE_TOP/dpdk/build
   
2. scp modules and scripts. You will need:
    $WORKSPACE_TOP/kernelight/drivers/lightfield/core/lf.ko
    $WORKSPACE_TOP/spdk/examples/nvme/perf/perf
    $WORKSPACE_TOP/spdk/scripts/setup.sh
    $WORKSPACE_TOP/spdk/include/spdk/pci_ids.h
    # If you're not loading rootfs_product, and want to work with lightfield, you should also upload:
    $WORKSPACE_TOP/lightfield/utils/lf_debug

3. Setup
    insmod lf.ko
    ./setup.sh --lightbox
    #TBD - completion reloacator config

4. Run the test.
Examples:
    1. Simple iops test(70-30):
        ./perf -q 128 -s 4096 -w rw -d 256 -c f -M 70 -t 5
    2. Use the fpga buffers :
        ./perf -q 128 -s 4096 -w rw -d 256 -c f -M 70 -a 61813169324032 -b 61778809585664 -t 5
        # fpga port address should be given in decimal-base, and can be obtined by using fpga_port_map.sh script
    3. Single write command test:
        ./perf -q 1 -s 4096 -w write -d 256 -c 1 -r 'trtype:PCIe traddr:0000:09:00.0' -n 1
